    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1938-09-02T11:44:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1938-09-02T11:44:00-05:00" n="686"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d686">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">882.6351 Bethlehem Steel Company/4:
                    Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Liberia</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Walton</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Monrovia</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1938-09-02T16:00:00-00:44"
                            >September 2, 1938—4 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received 1:30 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>63. Bethlehem Steel asks Liberian Government for geological survey and expresses
                    interest in future exploitation of the country’s iron ore. President will inform
                    corporation that arrangements have already been effected to make a survey.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Walton</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
